      • testAlterColumnNullability

        private void testAlterColumnNullability(java.sql.Statement st,
                                        boolean standardSyntax)
                                 throws java.sql.SQLException
        Test cases for altering the nullability of a column. Derby supports two different syntaxes: A legacy syntax for backwards compatibility (ALTER TABLE t ALTER COLUMN c [NOT] NULL), and SQL standard syntax (ALTER TABLE t ALTER COLUMN c SET NOT NULL, and ALTER TABLE t ALTER COLUMN c DROP NOT NULL).
        Parameters:
        st - a statement to use for executing SQL statements
        standardSyntax - if true, test the standard SQL syntax; otherwise, test the legacy syntax
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException - if a database error occurs
